  "description": "This dataset comprises functional near-infrared spectroscopy (fNIRS) neuroimaging data collected during a study investigating the neural mechanisms of morphine analgesia and placebo effects. Participants received painful electrical stimulation under three conditions: baseline pain, morphine administration, and placebo treatment. The study measured hemodynamic responses in the medial frontopolar cortex (medial BA 10) to characterize how morphine and placebo attenuate pain-related neural activity.",
  "methods_description": "fNIRS data were acquired during painful electrical stimulation under three experimental conditions: baseline pain, morphine administration, and placebo treatment. Hemodynamic responses were measured in the medial frontopolar cortex.",
